 been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":37,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":46,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":57,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1512, in Rowington, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Richard Baker. She died in Warwickshire, England."},"et":{"1512–":"1512–Surnud","1509–1558":"1509–1558","1535–1584":"1535–1584","1532–1571":"1532–1571","1512–Female":"1512–Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1512":"1512","1532":"1532","1584":"1584","1571":"1571","1509":"1509","1549":"1549","Rowington, Warwickshire, England":"Rowington, Warwickshire, England","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1512–":"1512–Kuollut","1509–1558":"1509–1558","1535–1584":"1535–1584","1532–1571":"1532–1571","1512–Female":"1512–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1535":"1535","1512":"1